 This install applies to "Globdule" © 1993 Psygnosis.

 This install requires WHDLoad and DIC to be in the path. Both can be found in
 the WHDLoad package.
 To install from a different drive than DF0: select installation mode Expert.

 The installed program requires 0.5 MB ChipMem and 1.5 MB OtherMem.
 It can be quit by pressing num '*' (key can be changed with Tooltype "QuitKey=").


 If you have problems with this installation please try and get a newer
 version of this package from the WHDLoad WWW-Page. If that doesn't help try
 some Tooltypes like NOCACHE, NOAUTOVEC, NOVBRMOVE, NOMMU, PAL or NTSC. If
 that also fails, please inform the author via the Bug-Report-Form which
 can be accessed on the WHDLoad WWW-Page or create a mantis issue directly
 at http://mantis.whdload.de

 For the full WHDLoad package, other installs and updates refer to:
	http://www.whdload.de/
 or	aminet:dev/misc/whdload#?
 and	aminet:game/patch/

 version 2.0 (07.01.2021) done by JOTD:
 - protection screen completely skipped (issue #0001330)
 - highscore save unless trainer is used (issue #0002955)
 - trainer infinite lives & energy
 - joypad/second button controls added


 version 1.2 (06.12.2020) done by JOTD:
 - added quitkey for 68000 machines (issue #0004855)
 
 version 1.1-B (24.06.2006) done by JOTD:
 - install script fixed

 version 1.1 (22.03.2006) done by JOTD
 - now uses fast memory
 - NTSC version supported
 - country check removed (now able to run NTSC version in PAL mode)
 - reworked readme/icons/install/slave source to 2006 standards
 - added nice icons by Chris/Frank/Exotica
 - source code included

 version 1.0 (1999) done by Mr Larmer
 - initial release
 - protection removed,
 - fast decrunching files
 - nice MWB/NI icons included

 Thanx to:
 - Jan Krolzig for original disk images.

 Joypad controls:
 - blue: switch item (space)
 - play: pause/resume (p)
 - green: start game (F1)
 - yellow: enter password (F2)
 - reverse+forward: give up (esc)
 - reverse+forward+yellow: quit to workbench (quitkey)
 